Sequence Information.Peptide Name: limnonectin-1Fb (natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals; XXU; 1S=S, UCSS1a)
Sequence Information.Source: the Fujian large-headed frog, Limnonectes fujianensis, China, Asia

Literature Information.Literature: Discovery: Discovered by "shotgun" cloning.Activity: Active against E. coli (MIC 70 uM) but not S.aureus adn C.albicans (MIC >160 uM).Toxicity: No hemo.lytic activity till 160 uM.Updated 5/2020; 7/2021
Literature Information.Author: Wu Y, Wang L, Zhou M, Ma C, Chen X, Bai B, Chen T, Shaw C.2011
Literature Information.Title: Limnonectins: A new class of antimicrobial peptides from the skin secretion of the Fujian large-headed frog (Limnonectes fujianensis).
